(208, 1, '2016-09-25 07:53:58', '2016-09-25 07:53:58', '[one_fifth]\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-180 size-full" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/1.png" alt="1" width="250" height="150" />\r\n\r\n[/one_fifth]\r\n\r\n[four_fifth_last padding="0 0 0 10px"]\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;"><em>Overview</em></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The <em>C8 Campaign</em> is a set off extensive programs and projects that will eventually define the specific calling and identity of the <em>JESUS: Sovereign Overcoming Shepherd</em> Christian Church.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">In a nut shell, this campaign may be called a total church program involving <em><strong>eight</strong> </em>major areas of ministries and purposes of Christians and a local Christian Church; and culminating in an adequate preparation of the body of the Lord Jesus Christ for the end-times, until the return of our dear Master and Savior.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;"><em>The 8 Major Components</em></span></strong></span></h3>\r\n<ol style="margin-left: 30px;">\r\n 	<li>Worship</li>\r\n 	<li>Evangelism</li>\r\n 	<li>Discipleship</li>\r\n 	<li>Fellowship</li>\r\n 	<li>Intercession</li>\r\n 	<li>Healing</li>\r\n 	<li>Temporal Excellence</li>\r\n 	<li>Community Outreach</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;"><em>The Cs and the 8s in the C8 Campaign</em></span></strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The <em><strong>C</strong></em> in C8 Campaign refers to the eight words that describe the believer of the Lord Jesus Christ in relation to each other and the local church, as well as their collective tasks</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The <em><strong>8</strong></em> in C8 Campaign, meanwhile, refers to the lessons and challenges the number eight (8) in the Bible present to the Christians, and the local church.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;"><em>The Three Phases of the Campaign</em></span></strong></span></h3>\r\nThis Campaign has three major phases; each of which has eight fundamental components. The three phases covers this year, 2014, and proceeds until the return of the Lord Jesus Christ.\r\n\r\nThe <strong><em><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #521a1a;">First Phase</span></em></strong> is perceived to be the longest. It focuses on the eight major components of what is supposed to be the main tasks and privileges of a truly maturing and well-rounded Christian church.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #521a1a;"><strong><em>Second Phase</em></strong></span>is actually an extension of the eight thrust/component of the First Phase, which is Community Outreach. This is about a comprehensive system of reaching out to communities, beginning with Angono where the JSOS Main is located. It will then proceed to reach out communities where the official JSOS Christian Church members reside. Finally, this Second Phase will focus on establishing daughter churches and/or ministry satellites as the Lord leads.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #521a1a;"><strong><em>Third Phase</em></strong></span> of the <em>C8</em> Campaign will occur much later. It will focus on eight major thrusts that will network with other churches and denominations in evangelizing peoples and communities, in assisting in the mobilization of Christian organizations to spread the gospel further, and in the preparation of the body of Christ for the coming escathological events.\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><strong><span style="color: #993300;"><em>The Simple Beginning</em></span></strong></span></h3>\r\nThe vision and mission for the <em>C8</em> Campaign were initially presented through a series of sermons last <em>September, 2013.</em>\r\n\r\nIf and when considerably implemented together by the local church, the <em>C8</em> Campaign, will certainly be a mighty tool of our great God in effecting a well-rounded, and growing church, both in quality and quantity, in its local setting.\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 50px;">[/four_fifth_last]</h3>', 'C8 Campaign', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '192-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-25 07:53:58', '2016-09-25 07:53:58', '', 192, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/09/25/192-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
