is now the subject of divine commendation</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p">The death and resurrection of Jesus Christ represent the outward provision for mans salvation. The term justification has reference to the way in which the saying benefits of Christs death are made available for the individual. Faith is the means whereby the sinner lays hold of the benefit.</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Church"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that the church is the body of Christ, the habitation of God through the Holy Spirit with divine appointment for the fulfillment of her great commission. Every genuine Christian believer is an integral part of it. <em>( Ephesians 1L22,23; Hebrews 12;23 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  ORDINANCES OF THE CHURCH</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;">We believe that the Lord Jesus Christ has given the collective body of Christian believers two specific ordinances which we must do:</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>1. BAPTISM IN WATER</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">This is to declare to the world that we have died with Christ and that we also have been raised with Him to walk in the newness of life.<em> ( Matthew 28:19; Acts 10:47,48; Romans 6:4 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>2. LORD''S SUPPER</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">This ordinance is to (1) symbolize our sharing the divine nature of our Lord Jesus Christ <em>( 2 Peter 1:4 )</em>; (2) to commemorate His death <em>( 1 Corinthians 11:26 )</em>; and (3) to anticipate His return <em>( 1 Corinthians 11:26 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Second Coming of the Lord Jesus Christ"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe in the literal, personal, glorious and pre-millennial return of the Lord Jesus Christ<em> ( 1 Corinthians 15:51-57; Acts 1;11; 1 Thessalonians 4:13-18 ).</em> We further believe of the following in relation to His return:</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  TRANSLATION OR RAPTURE</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 60px;">We believe that in His coming, those who have died in Christ will be resurrected to be translated together with those who are still alive to meet JESUS in the air and to be with Him. <em>( 1 Thessalonians 4:16,17; Romans 8:23; Titus 2:13 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 60px;">The rapture will include all true Christians since the beginning of time, from all nations, cultures, denominations and sects.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>B.  THE MILLENNEAL REIGN</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 60px;">We believe that after His return here, Jesus will reign with the saints on earth for one thousand years. <em>( Matthew 24:27-30; Revelations 1:7; 19:11-14 )</em>. Jerusalem will be His capital of rule. At this time, the worlds population will continue to expand. Christians will be given specific positions and leadership tasks to fulfill.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>C.  THE FINAL JUDGMENT</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 60px;">There will be a final judgment in which the wicked dead will be raised and judged according to their works. Whoever is not found written in the Book of Life will be consigned to everlasting punishment in the lake of fire.<em> ( Matthew 25:46; Mark 9:43-49; Revelations 19:20; 20:11-15; 21:8 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Biblical and Comprehensive Worship"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that God desires to be praised and worshipped always specially by those who already know Him personally in the light of the Bible. ( John 4:20-24 ) In fact, we believe that worship is the main reason for mans creation, existence and salvation . The main components of true worship is in truth and spirit.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  WORSHIP IN TRUTH</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;">To worship God in truth is to worship Him in the light of His word, the Holy Bible.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>1.  LIVING A RIGHTEOUS LIFE ( SANCTIFICATION )</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">By living in accordance to Gods commandments and directives, one is able to really worship and glorify God. This is the life that goes against the system of the world and is characterized by goodness, holiness and liveliness. <em>( Romans 12:1,2; Matthew 5:48 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>2.  SERVING GOD THROUGH ONES TALENTS AND SPIRITUAL GIFTS</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">We have been given various kinds of talents and skills. These are mainly meant to be used for glorifying God and edifying others. <em>( 1 Peter 4:9-10; 1 Corinthians 12 &amp; 14 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>3.  ABOUNDING IN GOOD WORKS</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">Christians have been saved to abound in good works. They are in fact, Christs workmanship. <em>( Ephesians 2:6-9 )</em> We are commanded to abound in good works and are assured that our good works will never be in vain. <em>( 1 Corinthians 15:58; Galatians 6:9,10 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>4.  SUPPORTING THE WORKS OF GOD THROUGH FINANCIAL AND MATERIAL GIVING</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">Financial giving to support Gods works and workers, if done in an attitude of gratitude, love and cheerfulness, can be an effective way of worshipping God. This comes from a clear understanding that Gods works and workers here on earth need human participation to be fully accomplished and to be adequately supported, respectively. <em>( 2 Corinthians 8 &amp; 9; Philippians 4:9, 19 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>5.  WINNING SOULS IN CHRIST</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">Leading other people to Christ in acts of repentance and acceptance of Him, is one of the best ways to worship and glorify God. It brings exultations in the heavens and high honors to the holiness, wisdom, power and love of God towards men. <em>( John 1:35-51; Luke 15:7; Acts 3:19; )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">Soul-winning, therefore, is no just a Christian responsibility but a great Christian privilege as well. Its indeed a privilege to let others come to God as repentant sinners and grateful worshipers. <em>( Acts 1:8; 2 Corinthians 5:10-21; Matthew 24:14; 28:18-20; Luke 24:47 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>B. WORSHIP IN SPIRIT</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 30px;">To worship God in spirit is to worship Him from the depths of our inmost being: our hearts and mind. It is worship that is based on ones devotion and love to God. <em>( Matthew 22:37 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Biblical Praise"]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Divine Healing"]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tabs]</p>', 'Doctrinal Statement', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '368-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-05 10:56:19', '2016-10-05 10:56:19', '', 368, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/05/368-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(396, 1, '2016-10-05 10:57:42', '2016-10-05 10:57:42', '<p class="left-20p bottom-10">This is intended simply as a basis of fellowship among members of the JSOS Christian Church <em>( " . . . that we all speak the same things . . . " 1 Corinthians 1:10 ) .</em> The wordings here are not inspired or contented for but the truth set forth is held to be essential to a full gospel <em>Christian</em> ministry.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10">No claim is made that it contains all biblical truths for the obvious reason that this is merely a partial list. Hence, the list may be added upon with supplementary and additional statements in the future.</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-30">However, we strongly believe that this list is Bible-based and is helpful for the identify and growth of the <em>JSOS Christian Church.</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-30"></p>\r\n<p>[su_tabs vertical="yes" class="my-custom-tabs"]<br />\r\n [su_tab title="The Bible"]</p>\r\n<p>We believe in the scripture, both the Old and the New Testament comprising of books to be verbally inspired by God for men. These are inerrant ( faultless ) in writings and are thus the sole supreme authority in the rule of Christian faith and conduct <em>( 2 Timothy 3:16; 1 Thessalonians 2:13. 2 Peter 1:21 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n [su_tab title="God"]</p>\r\n<p>We believe in the one true God who has revealed Himself as the eternally Self- existent One, the Creator of heaven and earth, and the Redeemer of mankind. We further believe that this God reveals Himself to us in three distinctive existing persons: the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit <em>( Matthew 28:19; 2 Corinthians 13:14; John 14:16,17 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n [su_tab title="Jesus Christ"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe in the <em>Lord Jesus Christ as the eternal SON of GOD</em>. As such, we believe in His:</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A. </strong> Virgin Birth and Humanity<em> ( Matthew 1:23 ; Luke 1:31-35 )</em><br />\r\n <strong>B.</strong> Deity<em> (Hebrews 1:8 ; John 10:30 ; 20:28 )</em><br />\r\n <strong>C.</strong> Sinless life <em>( Hebrews 7:26 ; 1 Peter 2:22 )</em><br />\r\n <strong>D. </strong>Substitutionary and atoning death on the cross according to the Scripture <em>( 1 Corinthians 15:3 ; 2 Corinthians 5:21 )</em><br />\r\n <strong>E.</strong>  Bodily Resurrection from the dead<em> ( Matthew 28:16 ; Luke 24:39 ; 1 Corinthians 15:4 )</em><br />\r\n <strong>F.</strong> Ascension into heaven and exaltation to the right hand of God<em> ( Acts 1:9 ;11 ; 22 Philippians 2:9-11 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Holy Spirit"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that the Holy Spirit is a divine person possessing all the attributes of deity. We further believe the following regarding Him:</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  To the unbelievers</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;">  He convicts them of sin, righteousness and judgment<em> ( John 16:5-11 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>B.  To the believers</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>1.</strong> He baptizes them into the Body of Christ<em> ( 1 Corinthians 12:13 )<br />\r\n </em><strong>2.</strong> He causes their regeneration <em>( John 3:3-6 )<br />\r\n </em><strong>3. </strong> He indwells them<em> ( 1 Corinthians 6:14-16 )<br />\r\n </em><strong>4.</strong>  He fills them with Himself <em>( Ephesians 5:18 )<br />\r\n </em><strong>5.</strong>  He gives them spiritual gifts listed in the Bible for service in the church. <em>( 1 Corinthians 12:27-31 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Man"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that man was created in the image of God. However, he sinned and thereby incurred not only physical death but also spiritual death which is separation to God.<em> ( Genesis 1:26,27; 2:17; 3:6; Romans 5:12-19 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p">We also believe that man is a tripartite being, body, soul and spirit <em>( 1 Thessalonians 5:23 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Salvation"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that salvation is only possible because of Gods grace and initiative, which is through the shed blood of Jesus Christ on the cross for us .</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  Condition</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;">Salvation is received through repentance and faith towards the Lord Jesus Christ <em>( Luke 24:47; Romans 10:13-15; Ephesians 2:8,9 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>B. Evidence of Salvation</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;">The inward witness of salvation is the direct witness of the Holy Spirit <em>( Romans 8:16 )</em> in the light and context of Biblical promises on it. <em>( 1 John 5 )</em> The outward evidence to all men is a life of righteousness and true holiness. <em>( Ephesians 4:24; Titus 2:12 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Sanctification"]</p>\r\n<p>We believe that God desires sanctification for each of His child. Sanctification is an act of separation from that which is evil and of dedication unto God. <em>( Romans 12:1,2; 1 Thessalonians 5:3; Hebrews 13:13 )</em> This can be done by the power of the Lord Jesus Christ.</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Justification"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that Gods children are justified. Justification is to acquit, declare righteous and pronounce sentence of acceptance into which one enters by faith. Justification is primarily a change of position on the part of the sinner. Once condemned, he is now acquitted; once under divine judgment, he is now the subject of divine commendation</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p">The death and resurrection of Jesus Christ represent the outward provision for mans salvation. The term justification has reference to the way in which the saying benefits of Christs death are made available for the individual. Faith is the means whereby the sinner lays hold of the benefit.</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Church"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe that the church is the body of Christ, the habitation of God through the Holy Spirit with divine appointment for the fulfillment of her great commission. Every genuine Christian believer is an integral part of it. <em>( Ephesians 1L22,23; Hebrews 12;23 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-60p" style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>A.  ORDINANCES OF THE CHURCH</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;">We believe that the Lord Jesus Christ has given the collective body of Christian believers two specific ordinances which we must do:</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>1. BAPTISM IN WATER</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">This is to declare to the world that we have died with Christ and that we also have been raised with Him to walk in the newness of life.<em> ( Matthew 28:19; Acts 10:47,48; Romans 6:4 )</em></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>2. LORD''S SUPPER</strong></p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 left-80p" style="padding-left: 90px;">This ordinance is to (1) symbolize our sharing the divine nature of our Lord Jesus Christ <em>( 2 Peter 1:4 )</em>; (2) to commemorate His death <em>( 1 Corinthians 11:26 )</em>; and (3) to anticipate His return <em>( 1 Corinthians 11:26 )</em></p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]</p>\r\n<p>[su_tab title="Second Coming of the Lord Jesus Christ"]</p>\r\n<p class="bottom-10 top-10 left-60p">We believe in the literal, personal, glorious and pre