(448, 1, '2016-10-07 05:04:56', '2016-10-07 05:04:56', '<p>[su_animate type="fadeInUp"]</p>\r\n<p>[two_fifth padding="0 20px 0 0"]</p>\r\n<div class="float-left w-30 top-40 left-40p text-left">\r\n<h4><strong><em>Address</em></strong></h4>\r\n<p class="bottom-30">305 Rainbow Avenue, Rainbow Village, Angono, Rizal, Philippines, 1930</p>\r\n<h4><strong><em>Vision for a new lotand building</em></strong></h4>\r\n<p class="bottom-30">8th Street, San Martin Subdivision, Angono Rizal, Philippines, 1930</p>\r\n<h4><strong><em>Lots of Love Campaign</em></strong></h4>\r\n<p class="bottom-30">We are trying to raise <em><strong>P2M</strong> </em>for the lot and <em><strong>P5M</strong> </em>for the new <em>Church</em> building. </p>\r\n<p class="bottom-30">The dream is to be able to host<strong><em>Bible Art Exhibit</em></strong> locally that is readily accessible to each person who thirsts for the<em>Word of God. </em>The dream is to have our own<em>Recording Studio</em>for creating<em>Gospel Songs</em>to reach people across the globe.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n If you have the passion to help us with this vision, don''t hesitate to contact us. God bless you!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>[/two_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[three_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[su_gmap address="305 rainbow avenue rainbow village angono rizal philippines"]</p>\r\n<p>[/three_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>', 'Location', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 05:04:56', '2016-10-07 05:04:56', '', 82, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(449, 1, '2016-10-07 05:05:33', '2016-10-07 05:05:33', '<p>[su_animate type="fadeInUp"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_third]</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-113 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h3-300x168.jpg" alt="JSOS" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-87" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h1-300x168.jpg" alt="h1" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-112 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h2-300x168.jpg" alt="?????" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_third]</p>\r\n<p>[two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>The <em><strong>JSOS Christian Church</strong></em> had its obscure beginning way back in 1992.</p>\r\n<p>That was after <em>Pastor Jose C. Tacadena</em> and his family (composed of wife <em>Adelia</em>, and children <em>Jihrael</em> and<em>Jehannah</em> ) left Manila where they had lived and ministered for six years. Having arrived in <em>Angono, Rizal</em>where his parents live, the couple was encouraged to hold regular Bible studies there.</p>\r\n<p>The initial attendees were composed of that extended family ( parents <em>Domingo</em> and <em>Maria,</em> sisters <em>Lydia, Perla,</em><em>Rose</em> and <em>Tess,</em> and older brother <em>Romeo</em> and his wife sis. <em>Aida</em> ), and a few faithful friends and co-workers in<em>Christ</em> from their previous Manila ministry. ( sisters <em>Adah</em> and <em>Allaine Nicolas,</em> Baby and <em>Berna Aquino,</em> and<em>Jimmy Manarang</em> ).</p>\r\n<p>Later on, the turn of events confirmed God''s leading to establish a local church right in Rainbow Village. The house of<em> Domingo Tacadena</em> served as its house church then.</p>\r\n<p>The name <em><strong>JESUS; SUPREME OVERRULING SHEPHERD </strong><strong>C</strong>HRISTIAN </em>church was chosen after much prayer and deliberation among the original incorporators primarily as a testimonyof God''s overruling supremacy in character and deeds, His overruling ability over all creations and principalities, and his unending personal love for every one, particularly for His sheep.</p>\r\n<p>After five months of holding mere home Bible studies at the said house, the small group of believers finally had their first Sunday Morning Worship Service on <em>June 28, 1992. </em>Since <em>Tacadena''s</em> house was obviously not ideal for corporate worship, the <em>JSOS</em> initial members and leaders prayed for a larger area.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n With God''s mercy and provision, <em>Delfin Tacadena</em>, the pastor''s eldest brother, bought a lot with unfinished house in front of the original sight. <em>Brother Delfin</em> developed it and lent it tothe church to become it''s official church worship center.</p>\r\n<p>[/two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '317-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 05:05:33', '2016-10-07 05:05:33', '', 317, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/317-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(450, 1, '2016-10-07 05:06:28', '2016-10-07 05:06:28', '<p>[su_animate type="fadeInUp"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_third]</p>\r\n<p><img class="pic bw aligncenter wp-image-113 size-medium" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h3-300x168.jpg" alt="JSOS" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="pic bw alignnone wp-image-87 size-medium" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h1-300x168.jpg" alt="h1" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p><img class="pic bw aligncenter wp-image-112 size-medium" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h2-300x168.jpg" alt="?????" width="300" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_third]</p>\r\n<p>[two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>The <em><strong>JSOS Christian Church</strong></em> had its obscure beginning way back in 1992.</p>\r\n<p>That was after <em>Pastor Jose C. Tacadena</em> and his family (composed of wife <em>Adelia</em>, and children <em>Jihrael</em> and<em>Jehannah</em> ) left Manila where they had lived and ministered for six years. Having arrived in <em>Angono, Rizal</em>where his parents live, the couple was encouraged to hold regular Bible studies there.</p>\r\n<p>The initial attendees were composed of that extended family ( parents <em>Domingo</em> and <em>Maria,</em> sisters <em>Lydia, Perla,</em><em>Rose</em> and <em>Tess,</em> and older brother <em>Romeo</em> and his wife sis. <em>Aida</em> ), and a few faithful friends and co-workers in<em>Christ</em> from their previous Manila ministry. ( sisters <em>Adah</em> and <em>Allaine Nicolas,</em> Baby and <em>Berna Aquino,</em> and<em>Jimmy Manarang</em> ).</p>\r\n<p>Later on, the turn of events confirmed God''s leading to establish a local church right in Rainbow Village. The house of<em> Domingo Tacadena</em> served as its house church then.</p>\r\n<p>The name <em><strong>JESUS; SUPREME OVERRULING SHEPHERD </strong><strong>C</strong>HRISTIAN </em>church was chosen after much prayer and deliberation among the original incorporators primarily as a testimonyof God''s overruling supremacy in character and deeds, His overruling ability over all creations and principalities, and his unending personal love for every one, particularly for His sheep.</p>\r\n<p>After five months of holding mere home Bible studies at the said house, the small group of believers finally had their first Sunday Morning Worship Service on <em>June 28, 1992. </em>Since <em>Tacadena''s</em> house was obviously not ideal for corporate worship, the <em>JSOS</em> initial members and leaders prayed for a larger area.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n With God''s mercy and provision, <em>Delfin Tacadena</em>, the pastor''s eldest brother, bought a lot with unfinished house in front of the original sight. <em>Brother Delfin</em> developed it and lent it tothe church to become it''s official church worship center.</p>\r\n<p>[/two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>', 'History', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '317-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 05:06:28', '2016-10-07 05:06:28', '', 317, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/317-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2016-10-07 05:09:02', '2016-10-07 05:09:02', '<p>[su_animate type="fadeInUp"]</p>\r\n<p>The name <strong><em>JSOS</em> </strong>was not decided upon by the small group of Christian incorporators through haphazard thinking and careless discussion. Instead, the name came about as a result of deep individual and group prayers and meditation not only on the Bible but also on certain events preceeding the establishment of the church that bears the said name.<br />\r\n After much prayerful discussion that lasted months, the incorporators of the said group were one in testifying that the name, " <strong><em>JESUS: Sovereign Overcoming Shepherd</em></strong> " is God-given for the specific purposes He has stored for this church.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n [su_tabs vertical="yes" class="my-custom-tabs"]<br />\r\n [su_tab title="Sovereign"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class="pic brighten aligncenter wp-image-116 size-full" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_sovereign.jpg" alt="Sovereign" width="123" height="130" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>That God is sovereign does not take away the fact that He still has many enemies. In fact, we, Christians have many enemies ourselves beginning with the chief opponent himself, Satan. In the Bible, Satan has mobilized his demonic forces to oppose God''s people in every possible way. With God''s loving and sovereign permission, the devil uses problems, sicknesses, failures, other people and even nature and circumstances to overcome us. But praise God because Jesus overrules all of them! In fact, Satan has thrown everything to Jesus in his attempt to defeat our Great Shepherd. But JESUS walloped him repeatedly from the temptation in the wilderness ( Matthew 4:1-11 ) to his resurrection from the dead. (John 10:17,18; 20:1-31; Colossians 2;9-15) Jesus overruled demons, sicknesses, nature, evil plots and people in the course of His earthly life. He will continue to do so until the total annihilation of all His enemies.</p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [su_tab title="Overcoming"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class="pic brighten aligncenter wp-image-114 size-full" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_overcoming.jpg" alt="Overcoming" width="118" height="116" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>That <em>God</em> is sovereign does not take away the fact that He still has many enemies. In fact, we, Christians have many enemies ourselves beginning with the chief opponent himself, Satan. In the Bible, Satan has mobilized his demonic forces to oppose God''s people in every possible way. With God''s loving and sovereign permission, the devil uses problems, sicknesses, failures, other people and even nature and circumstances to overcome us. But praise God because Jesus overrules all of them! In fact, Satan has thrown everything to Jesus in his attempt to defeat our Great Shepherd. But JESUS walloped him repeatedly from the temptation in the wilderness (<em> Matthew 4:1-11</em> ) to his resurection from the dead. (<em>John 10:17,18; 20:1-31;Colossians 2;9-15</em>) Jesus overruled demons, sicknesses, nature, evil plots and people in the course of His earthly life. He will continue to do so until the total annihilation of all His enemies.</p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [su_tab title="Shepherd"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class="pic brighten aligncenter wp-image-115 size-full" src="http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_shepherd.jpg" alt="Shepherd" width="112" height="102" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>This is an already widely accepted fact through out the universal body of Christian believers. Ever since <em>King David</em> wrote and sung,</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>" The Lord is my shepherd; I shall not want " ( Psalm 23:1 ),</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>God''s people have learned to look up to the Lord as the shepherd who leads them in life. When <em>JESUS</em> became a man, He declared,</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>" I am the good Shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for his sheep . . . I know my sheep pand my sheep know me-just as the Father knows me and I know the Father-I lay down my life for the sheep. " ( John 10:11-15 )</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>As our shepherd, Jesus loves us and provides for our needs consistently.</p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [/su_tabs]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>', 'Truth Behind Its Name', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '327-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 05:09:02', '2016-10-07 05:09:02', '', 327, 'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/327-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
